Stealing%26quot%3B%3A%20Music%20Labels'%20AI%20Suits%20Create%20New%20Copyright%20Puzzle%20For%20US%20Courts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ECountry%20musician%20Tift%20Merritt's%20most%20popular%20song%20on%20Spotify%2C%20%26quot%3BTraveling%20Alone%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20ballad%20with%20lyrics%20evoking%20solitude%20and%20the%20open%20road.%20Prompted%20by%20Reuters%20to%20make%20%26quot%3Ban%20Americana%20song%20in%20the%20style%20of%20Tift%20Merritt%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20artificial%20intelligence%20music%20website%20Udio%20instantly%20generated%20%26quot%3BHoly%20Grounds%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20ballad%20with%20lyrics%20about%20%26quot%3Bdriving%20old%20backroads%26quot%3B%20while%20%26quot%3Bwatching%20the%20fields%20and%20skies%20shift%20and%20sway.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMerritt%2C%20a%20Grammy-nominated%20singer%20and%20songwriter%2C%20told%20Reuters%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bimitation%26quot%3B%20Udio%20created%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20make%20the%20cut%20for%20any%20album%20of%20mine.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20great%20demonstration%20of%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20this%20technology%20is%20not%20transformative%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20Merritt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20stealing.%26quot%3B%20Merritt%2C%20who%20is%20a%20longtime%20artists'%20rights%20advocate%2C%20isn't%20the%20only%20musician%20sounding%20alarms.%20In%20April%2C%20she%20joined%20Billie%20Eilish%2C%20Nicki%20Minaj%2C%20Stevie%20Wonder%20and%20dozens%20of%20other%20artists%20in%20an%20open%20letter%20warning%20that%20AI-generated%20music%20trained%20on%20their%20recordings%20could%20%26quot%3Bsabotage%20creativity%26quot%3B%20and%20sideline%20human%20artists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20record%20labels%20are%20worried%20too.%20Sony%20Music%2C%20Universal%20Music%20Group%20and%20Warner%20Music%20sued%20Udio%20and%20another%20music%20AI%20company%20called%20Suno%20in%20June%2C%20marking%20the%20music%20industry's%20entrance%20into%20high-stakes%20copyright%20battles%20over%20AI-generated%20content%20that%20are%20just%20starting%20to%20make%20their%20way%20through%20the%20courts.%20%26quot%3BIngesting%20massive%20amounts%20of%20creative%20labor%20to%20imitate%20it%20is%20not%20creative%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Merritt%2C%20an%20independent%20musician%20whose%20first%20record%20label%20is%20now%20owned%20by%20UMG%2C%20but%20who%20said%20she%20is%20not%20financially%20involved%20with%20the%20company.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20stealing%20in%20order%20to%20be%20competition%20and%20replace%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuno%20and%20Udio%20pointed%20to%20past%20public%20statements%20defending%20their%20technology%20when%20asked%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%20They%20filed%20their%20initial%20responses%20in%20court%20on%20Thursday%2C%20denying%20any%20copyright%20violations%20and%20arguing%20that%20the%20lawsuits%20were%20attempts%20to%20stifle%20smaller%20competitors.%20They%20compared%20the%20labels'%20protests%20to%20past%20industry%20concerns%20about%20synthesizers%2C%20drum%20machines%20and%20other%20innovations%20replacing%20human%20musicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUNCHARTED%20GROUND%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%2C%20which%20have%20both%20attracted%20venture%20capital%20funding%2C%20have%20said%20they%20bar%20users%20from%20creating%20songs%20explicitly%20mimicking%20top%20artists.%20But%20the%20new%20lawsuits%20say%20Suno%20and%20Udio%20can%20be%20prompted%20to%20reproduce%20elements%20of%20songs%20by%20Mariah%20Carey%2C%20James%20Brown%20and%20others%20and%20to%20mimic%20voices%20of%20artists%20like%20ABBA%20and%20Bruce%20Springsteen%2C%20showing%20that%20they%20misused%20the%20labels'%20catalog%20of%20copyrighted%20recordings%20to%20train%20their%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMitch%20Glazier%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20music%20industry%20trade%20group%20the%20Recording%20Industry%20Association%20of%20America%20(RIAA)%2C%20said%20that%20the%20lawsuits%20%26quot%3Bdocument%20shameless%20copying%20of%20troves%20of%20recordings%20in%20order%20to%20flood%20the%20market%20with%20cheap%20imitations%20and%20drain%20away%20listens%20and%20income%20from%20real%20human%20artists%20and%20songwriters.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BAI%20has%20great%20promise%20-%20but%20only%20if%20it's%20built%20on%20a%20sound%2C%20responsible%2C%20licensed%20footing%2C%26quot%3B%20Glazier%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20cases%2C%20Warner%20Music%20referred%20Reuters%20to%20the%20RIAA.%20Sony%20and%20UMG%20did%20not%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20labels'%20claims%20echo%20allegations%20by%20novelists%2C%20news%20outlets%2C%20music%20publishers%20and%20others%20in%20high-profile%20copyright%20lawsuits%20over%20chatbots%20like%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%20and%20Anthropic's%20Claude%20that%20use%20generative%20AI%20to%20create%20text.%20Those%20lawsuits%20are%20still%20pending%20and%20in%20their%20early%20stages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20sets%20of%20cases%20pose%20novel%20questions%20for%20the%20courts%2C%20including%20whether%20the%20law%20should%20make%20exceptions%20for%20AI's%20use%20of%20copyrighted%20material%20to%20create%20something%20new.%20The%20record%20labels'%20cases%2C%20which%20could%20take%20years%20to%20play%20out%2C%20also%20raise%20questions%20unique%20to%20their%20subject%20matter%20-%20music.%20The%20interplay%20of%20melody%2C%20harmony%2C%20rhythm%20and%20other%20elements%20can%20make%20it%20harder%20to%20determine%20when%20parts%20of%20a%20copyrighted%20song%20have%20been%20infringed%20compared%20to%20works%20like%20written%20text%2C%20said%20Brian%20McBrearty%2C%20a%20musicologist%20who%20specializes%20in%20copyright%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMusic%20has%20more%20factors%20than%20just%20the%20stream%20of%20words%2C%26quot%3B%20McBrearty%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20pitch%2C%20and%20it%20has%20rhythm%2C%20and%20it%20has%20harmonic%20context.%20It's%20a%20richer%20mix%20of%20different%20elements%20that%20make%20it%20a%20little%20bit%20less%20straightforward.%26quot%3B%20Some%20claims%20in%20the%20AI%20copyright%20cases%20could%20hinge%20on%20comparisons%20between%20an%20AI%20system's%20output%20and%20the%20material%20allegedly%20misused%20to%20train%20it%2C%20requiring%20the%20kind%20of%20analysis%20that%20has%20challenged%20judges%20and%20juries%20in%20cases%20about%20music.%20In%20a%202018%20decision%20that%20a%20dissenting%20judge%20called%20%26quot%3Ba%20dangerous%20precedent%2C%26quot%3B%20Robin%20Thicke%20and%20Pharrell%20Williams%20lost%20a%20case%20brought%20by%20Marvin%20Gaye's%20estate%20over%20the%20resemblance%20of%20their%20hit%20%26quot%3BBlurred%20Lines%26quot%3B%20to%20Gaye's%20%26quot%3BGot%20to%20Give%20It%20Up.%26quot%3B%20But%20artists%20including%20Katy%20Perry%20and%20Ed%20Sheeran%20have%20since%20fended%20off%20similar%20complaints%20over%20their%20own%20songs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuno%20and%20Udio%20argued%20in%20very%20similar%20court%20filings%20that%20their%20outputs%20do%20not%20infringe%20copyrights%20and%20said%20US%20copyright%20law%20protects%20sound%20recordings%20that%20%26quot%3Bimitate%20or%20simulate%26quot%3B%20other%20recorded%20music.%26quot%3BMusic%20copyright%20has%20always%20been%20a%20messy%20universe%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Julie%20Albert%2C%20an%20intellectual%20property%20partner%20at%20law%20firm%20Baker%20Botts%20in%20New%20York%20who%20is%20tracking%20the%20new%20cases.%20And%20even%20without%20that%20complication%2C%20Albert%20said%20fast-evolving%20AI%20technology%20is%20creating%20new%20uncertainty%20at%20every%20level%20of%20copyright%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWHOSE%20FAIR%20USE%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20intricacies%20of%20music%20may%20matter%20less%20in%20the%20end%20if%2C%20as%20many%20expect%2C%20the%20AI%20cases%20boil%20down%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bfair%20use%26quot%3B%20defense%20against%20infringement%20claims%20-%20another%20area%20of%20US%20copyright%20law%20filled%20with%20open%20questions.%20Fair%20use%20promotes%20freedom%20of%20expression%20by%20allowing%20the%20unauthorized%20use%20of%20copyright-protected%20works%20under%20certain%20circumstances%2C%20with%20courts%20often%20focusing%20on%20whether%20the%20new%20use%20transforms%20the%20original%20works.%20Defendants%20in%20AI%20copyright%20cases%20have%20argued%20that%20their%20products%20make%20fair%20use%20of%20human%20creations%2C%20and%20that%20any%20court%20ruling%20to%20the%20contrary%20would%20be%20disastrous%20for%20the%20potentially%20multi-trillion-dollar%20AI%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuno%20and%20Udio%20said%20in%20their%20answers%20to%20the%20labels'%20lawsuits%20on%20Thursday%20that%20their%20use%20of%20existing%20recordings%20to%20help%20people%20create%20new%20songs%20%26quot%3Bis%20a%20quintessential%20'fair%20use.'%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFair%20use%20could%20make%20or%20break%20the%20cases%2C%20legal%20experts%20said%2C%20but%20no%20court%20has%20yet%20ruled%20on%20the%20issue%20in%20the%20AI%20context.%20Albert%20said%20that%20music-generating%20AI%20companies%20could%20have%20a%20harder%20time%20proving%20fair%20use%20compared%20to%20chatbot%20makers%2C%20which%20can%20summarize%20and%20synthesize%20text%20in%20ways%20that%20courts%20may%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20consider%20transformative.%20Imagine%20a%20student%20using%20AI%20to%20generate%20a%20report%20about%20the%20U.S.%20Civil%20War%20that%20incorporates%20text%20from%20a%20novel%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20she%20said%2C%20compared%20to%20someone%20asking%20AI%20to%20create%20new%20music%20based%20on%20existing%20music.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20student%20example%20%26quot%3Bcertainly%20feels%20like%20a%20different%20purpose%20than%20logging%20onto%20a%20music-generating%20tool%20and%20saying%20'hey%2C%20I'd%20like%20to%20make%20a%20song%20that%20sounds%20like%20a%20top%2010%20artist%2C'%26quot%3B%20Albert%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20purpose%20is%20pretty%20similar%20to%20what%20the%20artist%20would%20have%20had%20in%20the%20first%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20on%20fair%20use%20last%20year%20could%20have%20an%20outsized%20impact%20on%20music%20cases%20because%20it%20focused%20largely%20on%20whether%20a%20new%20use%20has%20the%20same%20commercial%20purpose%20as%20the%20original%20work.%20This%20argument%20is%20a%20key%20part%20of%20the%20Suno%20and%20Udio%20complaints%2C%20which%20said%20that%20the%20companies%20use%20the%20labels'%20music%20%26quot%3Bfor%20the%20ultimate%20purpose%20of%20poaching%20the%20listeners%2C%20fans%2C%20and%20potential%20licensees%20of%20the%20sound%20recordings%20%5Bthey%5D%20copied.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMerritt%20said%20she%20worries%20technology%20companies%20could%20try%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20replace%20artists%20like%20her.%20If%20musicians'%20songs%20can%20be%20extracted%20for%20free%20and%20used%20to%20imitate%20them%2C%20she%20said%2C%20the%20economics%20are%20straightforward.%20%26quot%3BRobots%20and%20AI%20do%20not%20get%20royalties%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722699120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fqmi7qq58_billie-eilish-reuters_625x300_03_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fits-stealing-music-labels-ai-suits-create-new-copyright-puzzle-for-us-courts-6254598%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prompted%20by%20Reuters%20to%20make%20%26quot%3Ban%20Americana%20song%20in%20the%20style%20of%20Tift%20Merritt%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20artificial%20intelligence%20music%20website%20Udio%20instantly%20generated%20%26quot%3BHoly%20Grounds%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20ballad%20with%20lyrics%20about%20%26quot%3Bdriving%20old%20backroads%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fits-stealing-music-labels